  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Pat the<strong> capers </strong>dry<strong> </strong>with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>capers</strong> to the pan and cook for 6-7 min or until crispy, then season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Once crispy, transfer the<strong> crispy capers</strong> to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680535163097-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680535163097-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680535163097-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680535163097-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1680535163097-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the capers are cooking, peel and finely dice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680535167816-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680535167816-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680535167816-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680535167816-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1680535167816-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680535173501-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680535173501-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680535173501-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680535173501-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1680535173501-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, trim the woody ends off the <strong>asparagus</strong></p><p>Tip: Alternatively, bend the woody ends of the asparagus until they snap!</p><p>Chop the <strong>asparagus tips</strong> away from the stalks and set them aside, then finely chop the <strong>asparagus stalks</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680535179512-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680535179512-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680535179512-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680535179512-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1680535179512-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Once the onion and garlic has slightly softened, add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the tomatoes have completely softened</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped asparagus stalks </strong>and cook for 1 min</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1680535188884-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1680535188884-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1680535188884-x700.jpg",
